Around a spare unpainted table littered with red wine bottles of varying fullness six youths playing cards ? no! ? seven, including James, content for the moment in the company of his dear friends Joel and Anya on his left, their housemates, whom he doesn?t know, on his right, the mysterious mutton-chopped rogue Chris Vanderbilt by them, in the corner, and before him, directly across the table, the small and sad-eyed Baltic-looking girl, what?s her name? Evelyn, or what the others call her, Evy, though he doesn?t call her that, though he?d be willing to call her that, if she wanted him to? but she hasn?t complained.